	<h2>Icons</h2>
	<p>Iconography, or the symbolic depiction of Christ and the Saints, are a defining feature of Orthodox Christianity.  The seventh ecumenical council of the Church was convened to condemn the destruction and removal of icons from the church. The icons were defended as testimonies to the incarnation of God in Christ.  God became touchable and depictable in Jesus and through His incarnation and ministry He sanctified creation.</p>
