	<h2>Mary</h2>
	<p>Christ’s mother is greatly honored (as she prophesied in Luke 1:48 “Henceforth all generations shall call me blessed) for her role in our salvation.  She is honored as the Mother of God for it was through her that the Word of God took flesh and was born a child.  She is honored as the first among Christians because she was the first to receive Christ into her life and bear Him forth through Her life. Orthodox Christians do not worship anyone or anything but God. Orthodox Christians do give honor where God has ordained.</p>
